5\. Test Execution Pipeline

Tests execute at three cadences, each serving a different detection
purpose:

5.1 Per-Build Execution (Continuous)

Every code change triggers the full test suite. The pipeline stages
execute in order; a failure at any stage halts progression:

  -------- --------------- ------------------ ------------- -------------------
  **\#**   **Stage**       **Tests Run**      **Pass        **On Failure**
                                              Criteria**    

  **1**    Compile + Lint  Go vet,            Zero errors,  Build blocked. Fix
                           staticcheck,       zero warnings immediately.
                           TypeScript strict                
                           mode                             

  **2**    Unit Tests      All rule-level     100% pass     Build blocked.
                           tests across 8                   Specific rule
                           categories (\~208+               failure identified.
                           tests for 52 rules               Classified per
                           × 4 cases)                       Layer 1 taxonomy.

  **3**    Integration     API boundary tests 100% pass     Build blocked.
           Tests           across all four                  Service boundary
                           architectural                    issue classified as
                           layers                           Integration Defect.

  **4**    Acceptance      Four demo cases    4/4 pass,     P0 STOP. Critical
           Tests           end-to-end         \$0.00        defect filed. All
                                              tolerance     affected case types
                                                            blocked.

  **5**    Coverage Report Rule coverage      No regression Warning. Coverage
                           analysis, boundary in coverage   gap logged as
                           coverage check,                  Medium defect. Does
                           interaction matrix               not block build.
                           verification                     
  -------- --------------- ------------------ ------------- -------------------

5.2 Pre-Deployment Execution (Gate)

Before any deployment to staging or production, an enhanced test run
executes that goes beyond the per-build suite:

-   **Full regression:** Every test in the repository, not just those
    affected by the change. This catches unexpected side effects from
    code changes that appear unrelated.

-   **Data quality scan:** The Data Quality Engine runs its full suite
    against the target database, verifying no data issues have emerged
    since the last scan.

-   **Assumption verification:** All four Q-CALC assumption-sensitive
    tests run, and their results are logged with the assumption status
    (CONFIRMED vs ASSUMED) so reviewers can assess residual risk.

-   **Performance baseline:** Each acceptance test is timed. Any test
    that exceeds 2× its historical average triggers a performance
    investigation.

5.3 Periodic Execution (Scheduled)

On a defined schedule (initially weekly, adjustable based on operational
tempo):

-   **Historical comparison batch:** A stratified sample of legacy
    transactions is processed through NoUI and compared. Every
    difference is categorized per the Layer 1 taxonomy.

-   **Rule completeness audit:** The RMC section index is
    cross-referenced against the rules inventory. Any un-implemented
    provision is flagged.

-   **Synthetic stress tests:** Large-volume test runs (all 10,000+
    synthetic members) to detect edge cases not covered by the four demo
    cases.

6\. Test Failure Handling

Every test failure is a defect. It is never an inconvenience to be
worked around, never a false positive to be ignored, and never an
auto-resolution candidate. This is mandated by ADR-004: test failures
are defects to investigate, not auto-resolve.

6.1 Failure Classification

When a test fails, the failure is immediately classified using the
unified taxonomy from Layer 1:

  ------------------ -------------------------- --------------------------
  **Failure Type**   **Diagnosis**              **Action**

  **Test is correct, Expected value traces to   Fix the code. Defect
  code is wrong**    statute. Actual value does enters the prioritized
                     not. This is a Calculation backlog per Layer 1
                     Defect or Rule             severity/scope matrix.
                     Interpretation Defect.     

  **Code is correct, Code output traces to      Correct the oracle.
  test is wrong**    statute correctly.         Recalculate from scratch
                     Expected value in test has (not patch). Two-person
                     an error. This is an       verification on the new
                     Oracle Defect.             expected value.

  **Both are wrong** Neither output matches     Return to Layer 1 Stage 2
                     statute. This typically    (Rule Derivation).
                     means a Rule               Re-derive from governing
                     Interpretation Defect that document. Both code and
                     infected both the          oracle rebuilt.
                     implementation and the     
                     test oracle.               

  **Data is wrong**  Test fixture contains      Correct the fixture.
                     incorrect input data       Verify no other fixtures
                     (wrong salary record,      share the same data error.
                     missing employment         
                     period). Code and oracle   
                     may both be correct.       

  **Infrastructure   Test failed due to service Retry. If persistent,
  failure**          unavailability, timeout,   investigate
                     or environment issue. Not  infrastructure. Do not
