7\. AI-Accelerated Test Generation

AI plays a specific, bounded role in the test framework: generating
draft test cases from certified rule definitions. AI does not determine
what is correct---it proposes tests that humans verify. This aligns with
ADR-002 (rules governance SDLC) and ADR-003 (AI learns orchestration,
not rules).

7.1 What AI Generates

-   **Test case templates** from YAML rule definitions: given a rule's
    conditions, formula, and tier applicability, AI proposes the four
    required cases plus additional edge cases.

-   **Boundary identification:** AI analyzes rule conditions to find all
    numeric thresholds and generates boundary/just-below pairs for each.

-   **Cross-rule scenarios:** AI reads the interaction matrix and
    generates composite test cases that exercise multiple interacting
    rules simultaneously.

-   **Regression scope recommendations:** When a rule changes, AI
    identifies which other rules depend on the changed rule and
    recommends which test suites to include in regression.

7.2 What AI Does Not Do

-   **AI does not calculate expected values.** Expected values come from
    hand calculations or statutory tables.

-   **AI does not decide if a test passes.** Pass/fail is a
    deterministic comparison against the oracle.

-   **AI does not suppress or modify failing tests.** This would violate
    ADR-004.

-   **AI does not certify test cases.** AI drafts; humans certify. Same
    as rule governance.

7.3 Test Regeneration on Rule Change

When a rule definition is updated through the governed SDLC:

6.  **AI reads the new certified rule definition** and generates an
    updated test suite proposal.

7.  **The proposal includes:** new test cases, modified test cases (with
    diff), deprecated test cases (no longer applicable), and unchanged
    test cases.

8.  **A human reviews the proposal** and provides or verifies expected
    values for all new and modified cases.

9.  **The updated test suite executes** against both the old and new
    rule versions to verify temporal correctness.

10. **Results are packaged** for human review as part of the complete
    change package (Layer 1, Stage 5).

> *AI generates tests; humans verify oracles; machines execute; humans
> judge failures. This separation of concerns ensures no single point
> can introduce and mask a defect simultaneously.*

